{
  "texts": [
    "The reason seems to lie in the matching of cognitive task requirements to the information capabilities of saliency maps.",
    "In cueing studies, the key cognitive requirement is target detection -a process that primarily relies on information about where important features are located.",
    "Unfortunately, in the present review it was not possible to examine whether target detection was supported by saliency maps.",
    "This is because the target detection studies had to be eliminated for confounding the benefits of saliency maps with the benefits of AI per se (Cabitza et al., 2022; Cabitza et al., 2023; Natali et al., 2023).",
    "An implication for future user studies of saliency maps is that they should match the cognitive task requirements to the information capabilities of saliency maps."
  ]
}